-- CNPC Starts 9.1 Billion Yuan of Projects in Xinjiang Province, Daily Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-14T23:52:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/cnpc-starts-9-1-billion-yuan-of-projects-in-xinjiang-province-daily-says.html

          
          
             China National Petroleum Corp.
started construction on two projects in China’s northwest region
of Xinjiang with a combined investment cost of 9.1 billion yuan,
the China Daily reported.  
 The Chinese oil and gas company started building a 6.2
billion yuan natural gas network in the region’s south that is
expected to begin operation in 2012, the newspaper said, citing
an unidentified company official.  
 China National Petroleum also started a 2.9 billion yuan
fertilizer project in Korla city, China Daily said, citing Vice
President Zhou Jiping.  
          
          


  


        